[Line 115] '2. **Std Deviation Component**: `item * np.std(bins)` scales the standard deviation of the bins by the item size. This introduces a measure of variability in bin sizes, penalizing bins that are more uniformly sized (lower std) or rewarding those with higher variability (higher std).'

[Line 116] ''

[Line 117] '3. **Sinusoidal Components**: The function adds three sinusoidal terms, `np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))`, each scaled differently. The sine function oscillates between -1 and 1, introducing periodic variations in the priority score based on the ratio of the item size to each bin size. This adds complexity and helps in breaking ties when multiple bins have similar scores.'

[Line 118] ''

[Line 119] 'By combining these components, the function generates a priority score for each bin that considers both the size compatibility and variability, providing a balanced heuristic for bin packing.'

