### Implementation 1:
```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return np.log(bins + 1) * np.sin(np.pi * item / bins) + np.log(bins + 1) * np.sin(np.pi * item / bins)
```

### Implementation 2:
```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return (item - np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + (item - np.mean(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins)
```

### Implementation 3:
```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return np.log(item + 1) * np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.log(item + 1) * np.cos(np.pi * (item / bins))
```

### Implementation 4:
```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return (item / (bins + 1)) * np.log(bins + 1) + (item / (bins + 1)) * np.log(bins + 1)
```

### Implementation 5:
```python
def priority(item: float, bins: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:
    return np.tan(item - bins) * np.log(bins + 1) + np.tan(item - bins) * np.log(bins + 1)
```

### Implementation 6:
