    return (item * np.std(bins)) * np.exp(item - bins) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins)) + np.sin(np.pi * (item / bins))
```

### Implementation 4:
This function calculates the priority by combining the item size with the standard deviation of the bins, using exponential and sine functions to determine the score.

